Jeff Wicks, News24ben sasonof Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A Sandton man embroiled in a Facebook race row attempted to delete his controversial comments that landed him in hot water on Sunday.&nbsp; &nbsp;Ben Sasonof had posted comments on a picture of a packed Durban beachfront at the weekend.He wrote: &ldquo;Eh eh Wena&hellip;must have smelt like the inside of Zuma&rsquo;s asshole,&rdquo; with the apparent reference to President Jacob Zuma.His comments raised the ire of other Facebook users with sight of the post, who accused Sasonof of being a racist.In response to them condemning his comments, he wrote: &ldquo;So fuck you and your bf. Go suck on Zuma&rsquo;s dirty, tyrant asshole if you love it so much.&rdquo;Sasonof also lashed out at one of his detractors directly, calling him a monkey.&ldquo;Mohammed Jameel Abdulla you&rsquo;re a fuckin little idiot! Every person you tagged there is a friend of mine from school! I dated a black girl you fuckin idiot fuck! Stupid Monkey bastard you!&rdquo;Late on Sunday night, his comments had been removed from the picture of the Durban beach front.In an earlier interview with News24, Sasonof was strident in defence of his comments.&ldquo;I am not confirming anything and I am not giving you any story. This is all nonsense,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;There was not any comment made that was racially incurring. Once I was personally attacked and provoked and that is when I started to lose it a little bit and become aggressive&hellip;and swear at people. At no point was I racist,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;Please don&rsquo;t call me again,&rdquo; he said, before abruptly ending the phonecall.The ANC Youth League in eThekwini said that they would likely open a case of crimen injuria with city police this week. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.